    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jm.00159.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">4. Upper College St</name>
                    <name type="place">Nottingham</name>
                    <name type="place">England.</name>
                    <date when="1891-05-09">May 9th.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr Whitman</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I have been hoping ever since Christmas (when I usually send you the little yearly present from myself &amp; friend) 
                to have been able to do the same this year, but I am afraid I cannot, for I have been trying to change my way of life 
                this year &amp; earn my living differently to what I have done till now, and have not hitherto succeeded conspicuously. 
                So I must content myself with sending the
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jm.00160.jpg" type="verso"/>
                contribution of my friend, increased somewhat by help from two others.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With very best love</salute>
                <salute>Your affectionate friend</salute>
                <signed>Leonard M. Brown.</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Please remember me kindly to Mrs. Davis.<ptr target="n6113"/></p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_jm.00161.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_jm.00162.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
